Email Communication Phrases
(a) Opening a Formal Email
✅ Subject: Request for Project Update

Dear [Recipient’s Name],
I hope this email finds you well.
I am reaching out to inquire about…
I would like to follow up on…
I am writing to inform you that…
(b) Requesting Information or Action
Could you please provide an update on…?
I would appreciate it if you could send me…
May I request your input on…?
Could you kindly confirm…?
(c) Apologizing for Delays or Mistakes
I sincerely apologize for the delay in my response.
We regret any inconvenience this may have caused.
Please accept my apologies for the misunderstanding.
(d) Closing a Professional Email
Looking forward to your response.
Let me know if you need any further details.
Please feel free to reach out if you have any questions.
Best regards, / Sincerely, / Warm regards,
2. Phrases for Meetings and Discussions
(a) Starting a Meeting
Let’s get started, shall we?
Thank you all for joining today’s meeting.
The purpose of this meeting is to discuss…
Let’s begin with a quick review of our agenda.
(b) Giving an Update
As of now, we have completed…
We are currently working on…
The latest status of the project is…
We are ahead of schedule / behind schedule because…
(c) Asking for Opinions & Feedback
What are your thoughts on this?
Do you have any suggestions for improvement?
How do you see this affecting our goals?
Could you elaborate on that point?
(d) Handling Disagreements Politely
I see your point, but I believe we should also consider…
That’s an interesting perspective. However…
I understand your concern, but let’s explore some alternatives.
Let’s agree to revisit this after further analysis.
(e) Concluding a Meeting
To summarize, we have agreed on…
Our next steps will be…
Let’s set a follow-up meeting for…
Thank you all for your time and contributions today.
3. Client Communication Phrases
(a) Welcoming a Client
Welcome to our office. It’s a pleasure to meet you.
Thank you for taking the time to meet with us today.
We appreciate your interest in our services.
(b) Discussing Business
We have prepared a proposal based on your requirements.
Our team is confident that we can deliver the best solution for you.
We value your feedback and would love to hear your thoughts.
Let’s discuss how we can tailor our services to fit your needs.
(c) Addressing Client Concerns
I understand your concerns, and we are happy to address them.
We appreciate your patience while we resolve this issue.
Let me check with my team and get back to you shortly.
We are committed to providing the best service possible.
(d) Closing a Conversation Professionally
Thank you for your time and trust in our services.
We look forward to working with you.
Please feel free to reach out if you need further clarification.
We will send you the necessary details shortly.
